          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "49-IN-115",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.999
              },
              "free_text": [
                " We used two samples of natural",
                "indium with n=2.88*10**23 atoms/cm2 and n=5.86*10**23",
                "atoms/cm2, respectively. The measurements were",
                "performed both at room temperature and at 77 K. A",
                "75-g sample of indium, enriched to 99.9% in 115In, on",
                "loan from the ORNL Isotope Pool, was used for spin",
                "measurements."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The 10B-loaded liquid scintillation detector",
                "is located 56.7 m from the neutron source. The",
                "55-cell segmented detector can handle instantaneous",
                "counting rates up to 9 MHz per cell with a dead time",
                "of about 20 ns. The detector has an efficiency of 95%,",
                "85%, and 71% at neutron energies of 10 eV, 100 eV,",
                "and 1000 eV, respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The measurements were performed on flight path",
                "2, which views a gadolinium-poisoned water moderator",
                "and has a cadmium/ boron liner to reduce the number",
                "of low-energy neutrons emerging in the tail of the",
                "neutron pulse. After the moderator the neutrons are",
                "collimated to a 10-cm-diam beam inside a 5-m-thick",
                "biological shield. The neutrons then pass through a",
                "3He/4He ion chamber system that acts as a flux",
                "monitor. The neutron flux is measured by the monitor",
                "for each neutron burst, and these measurements are",
                "used to normalize the detector rates."
              ]
            }
          ],
